  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Pesticide Action Network Africa (PAN Africa) will use this grant to for capacity building, sharing information, and advocating for policy changes in order to prevent and eliminate the health and environmental impacts related to pesticide use in Africa. PAN Africa will support new groups in Mali, Burkina Faso and Benin to participate in PAN activities, organize a national roundtable in each country and create a working group focused on local themes for each country. PAN Africa promote leadership of women&apos;s groups in the region by organizing training sessions in Benin, Mali, and Senegal and exchange visits with members from PAN Asia to learn from best practices and appropriate technologies for sustainable agriculture projects. PAN Africa will disseminate information and facilitate communication to other organizations working on pesticide issues in the region.</narrative>
  </description>
